Source: libgtk2-ex-errortextdialog-perl
Section: perl
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 4)
Maintainer: Kevin Ryde <user42@zip.com.au>
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Homepage: http://www.geocities.com/user42_kevin/gtk2-ex-errortextdialog/index.html
Bugs: mailto:user42@zip.com.au

Package: libgtk2-ex-errortextdialog-perl
Architecture: all
Depends: perl (>= 5.8.1), libgtk2-perl, libglib-ex-objectbits-perl, libintl-perl, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Dialog for error messages in a TextView
 Gtk2::Ex::ErrorTextDialog presents error messages to the user in a
 dialog with a TextView widget.  Errors accumulate and you can scroll
 back to see previous ones, cut-and-paste parts, or save them all to a
 file.
